messages.messageBody:
Michelle there are  two  yahoo groups that had great information .
I am no longer a member and do not know how good they still are.
My son was 3 when I joined them 7 years ago. Lots of great information and alternative to  mainstream dentistry plus new
discoveries in how to cure or prevent cavities:http://health.groups.yahoo.com/group/veryyoungkidsteeth/
http://health.groups.yahoo.com/group/alternativekidsteeth/
Alex Polikowsky

messages.messageBody:
Sorry.
we have visited the dentist recently and i have been told that 2 of my children need dental work...extractions and fillings on baby teeth. i am reluctant and they are anxious. the dentist had a terrible "bed side manner" and i said to her that i felt condemend by her remarks that it was all the fault of a bad diet and asked her if there could be other factors....she was reluctant to admit this could be the case.
i remember a couple of years ago a yahoo group was set up and it was hosted by a dentist who offered advice on other options and treatments available.
thanks
blessings
michelle
